title: Somatina rufifascia
text: Somatina rufifascia is a <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Geometridae">Geometridae</a> <a href="Species%20description">first described</a> by <a href="William%20Warren%20%28entomologist%29">William Warren</a> in 1896. It is found in <a href="Queensland">Queensland</a>, Australia.
